"sentence\": \"\\\"Government Gangsters: ...Patel, Kash PramodCheck Amazon for Pricing.\", \"from\": 684, \"to\": 753, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 710, \"end\": 715, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vallabhbhai_Patel\", \"score\": 0.9999973179951253, \"rank\": 2.682012207644883e-06, \"text\": \"Patel\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vallabhbhai_Patel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vallabhbhai_Patel\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"\\\"Government Gangsters\", \"from\": 684, \"to\": 705}, {\"ngram\": \"Kash PramodCheck Amazon\", \"from\": 717, \"to\": 740}, {\"ngram\": \"Pricing\", \"from\": 745, \"to\": 752}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Yet as much as drag artists reenacting Leonardo da Vinci's \\\"The Last Supper\\\" is offensive to Catholics who adhere to the Church's teaching on sexuality, terming this a \\\"mockery\\\" to Christians the world over fails to fully interpret the meaning and significance of the event.\", \"from\": 755, \"to\": 1029, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 794, \"end\": 811, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.570565575767341e-20, \"text\": \"Leonardo da Vinci\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\"}, {\"begin\": 848, \"end\": 857, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.54045352800878e-14, \"text\": \"Catholics\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}, {\"begin\": 936, \"end\": 946, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999999454084915, \"rank\": 4.485482483819297e-08, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"drag artists\", \"from\": 770, \"to\": 782}, {\"ngram\": \"the Church's teaching\", \"from\": 872, \"to\": 893}, {\"ngram\": \"sexuality\", \"from\": 897, \"to\": 906}, {\"ngram\": \"a \\\"mockery\", \"from\": 921, \"to\": 931}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 947, \"to\": 956}, {\"ngram\": \"the meaning\", \"from\": 987, \"to\": 998}, {\"ngram\": \"significance\", \"from\": 1003, \"to\": 1015}, {\"ngram\": \"the event\", \"from\": 1019, \"to\": 1028}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Rather than ridicule, the drag show was performance art in service of political and theological goals: namely, to co-opt Christian imagery in the service of the sexual revolution and its progeny, an objective many Christians share.\", \"from\": 1030, \"to\": 1261, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1151, \"end\": 1160, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999999993274287, \"rank\": 6.723861023574986e-10, \"text\": \"Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}, {\"begin\": 1244, \"end\": 1254, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999999454084915, \"rank\": 4.485482483819297e-08, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"ridicule\", \"from\": 1042, \"to\": 1050}, {\"ngram\": \"the drag show\", \"from\": 1052, \"to\": 1065}, {\"ngram\": \"performance art\", \"from\": 1070, \"to\": 1085}, {\"ngram\": \"service\", \"from\": 1089, \"to\": 1096}, {\"ngram\": \"political and theological goals\", \"from\": 1100, \"to\": 1131}, {\"ngram\": \"the service\", \"from\": 1172, \"to\": 1183}, {\"ngram\": \"the sexual revolution\", \"from\": 1187, \"to\": 1208}, {\"ngram\": \"its progeny\", \"from\": 1213, \"to\": 1224}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If there is any intended \\\"mockery\\\" in the event, it stems less from the performers and those celebrating it, and more from a source far more sinister.\", \"from\": 1262, \"to\": 1412, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"any intended \\\"mockery\", \"from\": 1274, \"to\": 1295}, {\"ngram\": \"the event\", \"from\": 1300, \"to\": 1309}, {\"ngram\": \"the performers\", \"from\": 1330, \"to\": 1344}, {\"ngram\": \"a source\", \"from\": 1385, \"to\": 1393}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For starters, we should rememberthat there are millions of self-professed Catholics who believe people of all sexual identities, proudly engaging in all manner of sexual behaviors, should be welcomed and celebrated \\\"at the Eucharistic table,\\\" as it were.\", \"from\": 1414, \"to\": 1668, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1488, \"end\": 1497, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.54045352800878e-14, \"text\": \"Catholics\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"starters\", \"from\": 1418, \"to\": 1426}, {\"ngram\": \"millions\", \"from\": 1461, \"to\": 1469}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 1510, \"to\": 1516}, {\"ngram\": \"all sexual identities\", \"from\": 1520, \"to\": 1541}, {\"ngram\": \"all manner\", \"from\": 1563, \"to\": 1573}, {\"ngram\": \"sexual behaviors\", \"from\": 1577, \"to\": 1593}, {\"ngram\": \"the Eucharistic table\", \"from\": 1633, \"to\": 1654}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Catholic organizations such asDignityUSAandNew Ways Ministryaffirm LGBTQIA+ identities and their full acceptance into the entirety of the sacramental life of the Church, while Catholic academic institutions such asNotre Dame,Loyola University Chicago, andUniversity of San Diegohave hosted drag shows.\", \"from\": 1669, \"to\": 1970, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1669, \"end\": 1677, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholicity\", \"score\": 0.9998255526557356, \"rank\": 0.00017447778096455036, \"text\": \"Catholic\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholicity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholicity\"}, {\"begin\": 1845, \"end\": 1853, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholicity\", \"score\": 0.9998255526557356, \"rank\": 0.00017447778096455036, \"text\": \"Catholic\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholicity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholicity\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Ways Ministryaffirm LGBTQIA+ identities\", \"from\": 1716, \"to\": 1755}, {\"ngram\": \"their full acceptance\", \"from\": 1760, \"to\": 1781}, {\"ngram\": \"the entirety\", \"from\": 1787, \"to\": 1799}, {\"ngram\": \"the sacramental life\", \"from\": 1803, \"to\": 1823}, {\"ngram\": \"the Church\", \"from\": 1827, \"to\": 1837}, {\"ngram\": \"such asNotre Dame\", \"from\": 1876, \"to\": 1893}, {\"ngram\": \"San Diegohave\", \"from\": 1938, \"to\": 1951}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Though it pains me to write it,most self-identifying Catholicsin Europe and even the United States say homosexuality should be accepted and that gays should be allowed to marry.\", \"from\": 1971, \"to\": 2148, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2036, \"end\": 2042, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Union\", \"score\": 0.8723056271854394, \"rank\": 0.1463868843394636, \"text\": \"Europe\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Union\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Union\"}, {\"begin\": 2056, \"end\": 2069, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.999643736155798, \"rank\": 0.0003563880600691229, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"homosexuality\", \"from\": 2074, \"to\": 2087}, {\"ngram\": \"gays\", \"from\": 2116, \"to\": 2120}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If you think that's bad, consider the doctrines and praxis of many Protestant denominations.\", \"from\": 2150, \"to\": 2242, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the doctrines\", \"from\": 2184, \"to\": 2197}, {\"ngram\": \"praxis\", \"from\": 2202, \"to\": 2208}, {\"ngram\": \"many Protestant denominations\", \"from\": 2212, \"to\": 2241}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Episcopal Church, Evangelical Lutheran Church in America, Presbyterian Church in the United States of America, and the United Church of Christ, among other American denominations,expressly affirm gay marriage.\", \"from\": 2243, \"to\": 2456, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2243, \"end\": 2263, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Episcopal_Church_(United_States)\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"The Episcopal Church\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Episcopal_Church_(United_States)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Episcopal_Church_(United_States)\"}, {\"begin\": 2265, \"end\": 2285, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lutheranism\", \"score\": 0.5902727874212497, \"rank\": 0.6941319692219543, \"text\": \"Evangelical Lutheran\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lutheranism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lutheranism\"}, {\"begin\": 2305, \"end\": 2317, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Presbyterianism\", \"score\": 0.973661734328189, \"rank\": 0.02705071397190968, \"text\": \"Presbyterian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Presbyterianism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Presbyterianism\"}, {\"begin\": 2403, \"end\": 2411, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999996717047536, \"rank\": 1.823463816676231e-07, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\